<subSubSection id="209E1AAD0D6FB26AFF66FC76FE5310DF" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="683B49260D6FB26DFF66FC76FE4214BD" blockId="3.[151,779,942,1005]" box="[151,435,978,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
(
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFF6EFC76FEC414BD" box="[159,309,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Figures 2a–d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFEB1FC77FE5B14BD" box="[320,426,978,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Four species of Crossomeles. a) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of head. b) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of head. c) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of head. d) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of head. e) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. f) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. g) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of pronotum. h) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of pronotum. i) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. j) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. k) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of metatibia. l) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577714/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">5d, 5h, 5l</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="683B49260D6FB26DFF66FBBFFE0A132D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1050,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF66FBBFFED01364" bold="true" box="[151,289,1050,1076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Description</emphasis>
. Male (
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFE89FBBEFE001365" box="[376,497,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Figs. 2a–d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFE0DFBBFFDBB1366" box="[508,586,1050,1078]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Four species of Crossomeles. a) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of head. b) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of head. c) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of head. d) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of head. e) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. f) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. g) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of pronotum. h) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of pronotum. i) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. j) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. k) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of metatibia. l) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577714/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">5d, h, i</figureCitation>
). Length 18.0 mm (measured from frons to abdominal apex), width 
<quantity id="AF7CE4C30D6FB26DFAB6FBBEFA6C1365" box="[1351,1437,1051,1077]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
(measured across humeri). Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFD9AFB9AFD4C1309" box="[619,701,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
. Form moderate sized, elongate; integument black with portions dark brown and reddish orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="683B49260D6FB26DFF36FB23FD351229" blockId="3.[151,1437,1050,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36FB23FEFD13F1" bold="true" box="[199,268,1158,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36FB23FEF413F1" bold="true" box="[199,261,1158,1185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Frons black with fine, somewhat abundant yellow pubescence; eyes large, globose, narrowly separated in front by about 5 ommatidia; frons with narrow, moderately deep median suture; genae about 3/4 as tall as lower eye lobe (
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFEF8FB6AFE9713B9" box="[265,358,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Figs. 2c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFE84FB6BFE6513B9" box="[373,404,1230,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Four species of Crossomeles. a) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of head. b) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of head. c) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of head. d) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of head. e) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. f) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. g) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of pronotum. h) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of pronotum. i) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. j) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. k) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of metatibia. l) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577714/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">5d</figureCitation>
); vertex irregularly punctate; antennae extending to near middle of abdominal segment II; antennomeres I–IV black, V–XI dark brown; antennomeres I–VI with several long and erect setae beneath, VI–XI slightly expanded apically; with 2–3 small sensory pores on dorsal and ventral surface of each antennomere. Antennal formula based on length of antennomere III: scape=0.50; II=0.25; III=1.00; IV=0.50; V=0.90; VI=0.85; VII=0.83; VIII=0.70; IX=0.65; X=0.60; XI=0.65.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="683B49260D6FB26DFF36FA27FD8F1079" blockId="3.[151,1437,1050,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36FA27FED512CD" bold="true" box="[199,292,1410,1437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36FA27FEEC12CD" bold="true" box="[199,285,1410,1437]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum black, elongate, subcylindrical, about 1.25 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFB59FA26FAD612CD" box="[1192,1319,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Figs. 2a, b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFAC7FA27FAA412CD" box="[1334,1365,1410,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Four species of Crossomeles. a) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of head. b) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of head. c) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of head. d) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of head. e) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. f) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. g) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of pronotum. h) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of pronotum. i) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. j) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. k) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of metatibia. l) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577714/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">5h</figureCitation>
); disk coarsely, deeply, subconfluently alveolate, pubescence yellow across apex, base, and down sides dense; prosternum clothed with long, suberect setae; mesoventrite densely clothed at sides with fine, golden, appressed pubescence; metaventrite moderately densely punctate, moderately densely clothed with short, golden, appressed pubescence along top margin and on posterior end. Mesanepisternum densely clothed with appressed pale yellow pubescence. Mesepimeron with sparse pale yellow setae. Metanespisternum with sparse pale yellow setae on anterior 3/4, densely clothed with appressed pale yellow pubescence on posterior 1/4. Scutellum densely clothed with appressed pale yellow pubescence. Elytra extending beyond posterior margin of abdominal segment I at about middle of segment II; disk shining, testaceous, base yellowish inside of humeri, humeri black, margins narrowly black; punctures moderately dense, becoming finer toward apex; pubescence sparse, long, erect and suberect, each seta rising out of a puncture; each elytron strongly dehiscent and narrowing from behind middle; apices narrowly rounded, about as wide as length of second antennal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="683B49260D6FB26DFF36F896FE8110E9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1050,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36F896FEF4101D" bold="true" box="[199,261,1843,1869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D6FB26DFF36F896FF0C101D" bold="true" box="[199,253,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pro- and mesofemora reddish orange, pro- and mesotibiae almost black, basal half of metatibiae black; pro- and mesofemora strongly clavate, short; metafemora elongate, widening slightly at apical third (
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFAC6F8F2FA7E1022" box="[1335,1423,1879,1906]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
); metatibiae with a large, dense brush of orangish hairs on apical two-thirds (
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D6FB26DFC14F8DEFBC310C5" box="[997,1074,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[158,1429,181,1720]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Four species of Crossomeles. a) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of head. b) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of head. c) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of head. d) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of head. e) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. f) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of pronotum. g) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of pronotum. h) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of pronotum. i) C. acutipennis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. j) C. aureopilis, paratype male, close-up of metatibia. k) C. copei, holotype male, close-up of metatibia. l) C. oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male, close-up of metatibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577714/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5i</figureCitation>
). Metatarsomere I about as long as II–IV combined.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3CFB19AE0D68B26AFF66F903FE5A11B2" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" startId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" targetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" targetPageId="4">
