<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFF66F903FEE211EE" bold="true" box="[151,275,1702,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="AF8432A50D68B26AFEE8F903FDD811EE" authority="Nearns &amp; Swift, 2022" authorityName="Nearns &amp; Swift" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,553,1702,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Crossomeles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oscarcastilloi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFEE8F903FDD811EE" box="[281,553,1702,1726]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Crossomeles oscarcastilloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFDDEF903FD8E11EE" bold="true" box="[559,639,1702,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41C3284F0D68B26AFDDEF903FD8E11EE" box="[559,639,1702,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype male. 
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFCD9F903FCCF11EE" bold="true" box="[808,830,1702,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">a)</emphasis>
Dorsal habitus. 
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFC12F903FC0B11EE" bold="true" box="[995,1018,1702,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">b)</emphasis>
Photograph of live holotype. 
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFAD6F903FACA11EE" bold="true" box="[1319,1339,1702,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">c)</emphasis>
Close-up of head. 
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFF1EF96FFEF711B2" bold="true" box="[239,262,1738,1762]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">d)</emphasis>
Lateral habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="683B49260D68B26AFF36F8A8FE89103D" blockId="4.[151,1437,1805,2040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFF36F8A8FECD1078" bold="true" box="[199,316,1805,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Elongate, slender, broadening slightly toward apex, with portions reddish orange, yellow and black (
<figureCitation id="F0BF55A30D68B26AFF6EF895FEED101B" box="[159,284,1840,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[258,1330,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Crossomeles oscarcastilloi sp. nov., holotype male. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Photograph of live holotype. c) Close-up of head. d) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577708/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Figs. 2a, d</figureCitation>
); ventrites progressively more densely punctate from first; pubescence sparse; last ventrite shallowly impressed medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="683B49260D68B26AFF36F8D0FE5310DF" blockId="4.[151,1437,1805,2040]" box="[199,418,1909,1936]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFF36F8D0FED410C0" bold="true" box="[199,293,1909,1936]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFF36F8D0FEEF10C0" bold="true" box="[199,286,1909,1936]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="209E1AAD0D68B26AFF36F83DFC4410A8" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="683B49260D68B26AFF36F83DFC4410A8" blockId="4.[151,1437,1805,2040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="5AF095340D68B26AFF36F83DFE2B10E2" bold="true" box="[199,474,1944,1970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis and remarks</emphasis>
. This species can be separated from congeners by the elytra longer, extending beyond posterior margin of abdominal segment I to about middle of segment II, narrowly rounded apically; integument of basal antennae black; and genae about 3/4 as long as lower lobe of eye.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
